						               													<description>In space, no one can see you roll.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Dicewars is a lightweight game of deadly space combat that can be played anywhere you have polyhedral dice and a flat surface to play on.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To play Dicewars you&amp;rsquo;ll need a bunch of polyhedral dice, which you will use to make Starships. &amp;#10;Each player should have the same number of dice, but they don&amp;rsquo;t have to be the same types. &amp;#10;You&amp;rsquo;ll need at least one d20 per ship, and a few d6s for each one.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Dicewars is a quick tactical game that uses abstract positioning to represent swirling space battles on a flat surface with just the dice you probably have with you anyway (includes suggestions for making use of all sorts of weird and specialist dice you might have). &amp;#10;Play while you are waiting for your rpg group, play instead of your rpg, play instead of your more cumbersome wargames.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The ruleset includes full play references, diagrams, turn sequences, and suggestions on campaign rules.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
